The paper deals with the problem of urban land cover classification using deep convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to handle missing data modalities during testing, which involves embedding all available training modalities in the hallucination network. This approach involves using deep learning techniques and can be classified under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with environmental monitoring, which can be classified under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method to handle missing data modalities in real-time, which can be classified under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
